function clean_column(col::AbstractString)
    return lowercase(replace(strip(col), r" |-|" => "_"))
end
```
This function takes in a single argument `col`, which is expected to be a string. The `strip` function is used to remove any leading or trailing whitespaces. The `lowercase` function is then used to convert all the characters in the string to lowercase. Finally, the `replace` function is used with a regular expression `r" |-|"` to replace any spaces or hyphens with an underscore. The regular expression `r" |-|"` matches any space or hyphen character. The resulting string is then returned by the function.
